title: Selfish DNA
text: Not to be confused with the book The Selfish Gene.Selfish DNA is a term for sequences of DNA that sensu stricto have two distinct properties:  the DNA sequence spreads by forming additional copies of itself within the genome; and  it makes no specific contribution to the reproductive success of its host organism.

title: Socrates of Constantinople

title: Muggle

title: Black body

title: Typewriter
